</taxonomicName>
in the literature, but the present
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1439,258,604]" box="[151,1435,538,564]" pageId="8" pageNumber="213">
author divided the data into Atlantic records (
<taxonomicName box="[695,824,538,563]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="8" pageNumber="213" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="alveolus">
<emphasis box="[695,824,538,563]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="213">L. alveolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and Indo­Pacific records (
<taxonomicName box="[1152,1285,538,563]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="8" pageNumber="213" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="belknapi">
<emphasis box="[1152,1285,538,563]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="213">L. belknapi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
